1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:14,067
<i>You have to show them that
you can live all by yourself.</i>

2
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:16,167
<i> Don't forget that, Mookie.</i>

3
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:18,000
<i> You have to fight.</i>

4
00:00:18,133 --> 00:00:21,400
<i>In all instances,
you have to fight.</i>

5
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:22,500
<i> Why did you do that, Mookie?</i>

6
00:00:22,633 --> 00:00:23,867
<i>I thought you were different
from the rest.</i>

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,267
<i> That's enough, Mooks.</i>

8
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:27,600
<i>I wish I have the guts
to face my daughter.</i>

9
00:00:27,733 --> 00:00:29,333
<i> I miss her so much, Logan.</i>

10
00:00:29,467 --> 00:00:30,933
<i> DJ!</i>

11
00:00:31,067 --> 00:00:32,300
<i> One more, please!</i>

12
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:33,400
<i> That's Mookie's voice!</i>

13
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:35,000
<i>- Let's go!
- What do you want?</i>

14
00:00:35,167 --> 00:00:36,633
<i>You don't want me
to be your friend anymore?</i>

15
00:00:36,767 --> 00:00:38,000
<i> Then don't!</i>

16
00:00:38,133 --> 00:00:39,600
<i>Nobody's forcing you to do this!</i>

17
00:00:39,733 --> 00:00:41,467
<i>Why are you still so affected
with Emma?</i>

18
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:43,900
<i>How can you forget about her
if you still keep those?</i>

19
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:45,633
<i> I am worried about Mookie.</i>

20
00:00:45,767 --> 00:00:48,233
<i>I think she is carrying
a heavy load.</i>

21
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:50,800
<i>And I am not beside her
to make things a bit lighter.</i>

22
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:51,867
<i> Emma!</i>

23
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:54,200
<i>- What do you want?
- I'm so sorry.</i>

24
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:56,067
<i>I thought you were someone
I know.</i>

25
00:01:37,533 --> 00:01:38,700
Emma...

26
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:41,033
What's up?

27
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,067
How have you been?

28
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:45,667
I want to come near her.

29
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:48,333
I want to confront her.
I want to hurt her!

30
00:01:48,467 --> 00:01:51,733
I want her to feel how much
she had hurt me!

31
00:01:51,867 --> 00:01:54,333
But when I saw her...

32
00:01:54,467 --> 00:01:55,333
Why did I back out?

33
00:01:55,467 --> 00:01:57,067
I wasn't able to do anything,
Logan!

34
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,200
It must be your trauma
from that woman.

35
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:03,867
She did a handful on you.

36
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,767
But don't you worry.

37
00:02:05,900 --> 00:02:09,300
The day will come when you will
be able to face your fears.

38
00:02:09,433 --> 00:02:12,667
Time will come when you can face
her without fear.

39
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:15,667
I became even more worried
about Mookie when I saw Jade.

40
00:02:17,233 --> 00:02:19,667
Maybe I can come near her
even just for a bit?

41
00:02:32,867 --> 00:02:34,867
I just saw this photo earlier.

42
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:38,600
I don't know what's happening
to her in Jade'shouse.

43
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:42,167
Whether she's happy,
or is she sad?

44
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:43,700
Is she going through something?

45
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:45,667
Did that woman do something
to her?

46
00:02:53,733 --> 00:02:57,200
We already have a venue
for Artemis's anniversary.

47
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:59,133
But we're just waiting
for confirmation.

48
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:03,900
Jade, if you need anything,
just let me know, okay?

49
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:07,533
Actually, there is.

50
00:03:07,667 --> 00:03:08,867
But it's not about the company.

51
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,000
It's...

52
00:03:10,133 --> 00:03:11,900
It's actually something
personal.

53
00:03:12,733 --> 00:03:15,267
Okay. Maybe I can help.
What's that?

54
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:18,000
You know Emma Joseco, right?

55
00:03:18,467 --> 00:03:19,600
Mookie's mom?

56
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:23,833
I need your help in finding her.

57
00:03:27,233 --> 00:03:28,233
Why?

58
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,700
I saw Emma at the mall earlier.

59
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:36,800
And...

60
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:41,567
she seemed different.

61
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:43,800
Her attire.

62
00:03:43,933 --> 00:03:45,600
Her stance.

63
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:51,267
Everything about her,
it's just different.

64
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:54,367
She's not the same Emma
that I knew.

65
00:03:55,767 --> 00:03:56,933
What do you mean?

66
00:03:58,233 --> 00:04:00,533
She's not like how she used to?

67
00:04:00,667 --> 00:04:03,900
Yes! Exactly!

68
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:07,933
And I wonder
how did that happen?

69
00:04:09,367 --> 00:04:11,733
How did she become
the way she is now?

70
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:15,433
I don't know.

71
00:04:15,567 --> 00:04:19,300
But why would you want
to find her?

72
00:04:19,433 --> 00:04:21,333
You're already a happy family,
right?

73
00:04:21,467 --> 00:04:23,933
And you are already engaged
with Danilo.

74
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:27,167
Well, yeah, that's true.

75
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:28,500
But...

76
00:04:28,633 --> 00:04:30,700
I am not like my sister, Ollive.

77
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:35,233
Of course, I still want Emma
to see her family.

78
00:04:35,367 --> 00:04:36,700
Just for closure.

79
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:38,500
And one more thing...

80
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:41,467
I don't want Mookie
to have grudges with Emma.

81
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:46,033
Because no matter what we say,
Emma is still her mother.

82
00:04:46,167 --> 00:04:50,000
Wow, Jade, you are so sweet
and thoughtful.

83
00:04:51,233 --> 00:04:53,400
It's good to know
that you are that compassionate.

84
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:55,700
Unlike Olive.

85
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:57,233
She was so paranoid
and overdramatic.

86
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:04,700
So, are you going to help me?

87
00:05:06,467 --> 00:05:07,167
Sure.

88
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:08,767
I will find Emma for you.

89
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:11,233
Thank you, Astrid.

90
00:05:11,367 --> 00:05:15,300
But can you please keep this
between the two of us?

91
00:05:16,067 --> 00:05:18,267
I want to surprise Danilo
and Mookie.

92
00:05:29,033 --> 00:05:34,867
Of course, I still want Emma
to see her family.

93
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,333
For closure.

94
00:05:37,467 --> 00:05:38,500
And...

95
00:05:40,033 --> 00:05:44,600
I don't want Mookie to keep
grudges with her mother,

96
00:05:44,733 --> 00:05:46,433
Emma, right?

97
00:05:46,567 --> 00:05:48,200
You are so gullible, girl!

98
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:51,100
Of course not!

99
00:05:51,233 --> 00:05:54,167
Why would I do that? Hello?

100
00:05:54,300 --> 00:05:57,567
I thought you have become weak.

101
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:00,733
Well, that's just drama!

102
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,733
Bravo, Jade!

103
00:06:04,867 --> 00:06:06,300
Bravo!

104
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:07,933
Of course!

105
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:09,600
More so now!

106
00:06:09,733 --> 00:06:12,367
Now that Danilo and I
are engaged!

107
00:06:13,767 --> 00:06:21,767
I will for sure not let Emma
ruin my family!

108
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:27,567
I know, right?

109
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:36,533
Mom Ligaya...

110
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:42,200
no matter how much tears
you shed,

111
00:06:42,367 --> 00:06:44,433
you cannot do anything.

112
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:48,400
This is your fault!

113
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:52,900
If you did not give me
away before,

114
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:58,767
maybe I would have loved you

115
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:03,000
the way I love Danilo
and Mookie.

116
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:07,467
I will do everything...

117
00:07:09,667 --> 00:07:12,533
if it means Danilo and Mookie
will stay with me forever.

118
00:07:14,733 --> 00:07:17,033
And I will do everything...

119
00:07:19,433 --> 00:07:22,433
to make sure Emma
will never ever meet

120
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,200
Danilo and Mookie ever again.

121
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:30,333
You will see.

122
00:07:35,033 --> 00:07:37,033
No, you won't see.

123
00:07:37,167 --> 00:07:41,367
Because you are trapped
inside here.

124
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,367
Don't worry.

125
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:46,467
I will keep you posted.

126
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,767
Goodbye!

127
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:06,467
Do you have what it takes
to be a cheer dancer?

128
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,700
If you really want to be
a cheer dancer,

129
00:08:11,067 --> 00:08:12,933
prove it!

130
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:14,300
Prove it all!

131
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:20,967
We will do a one-on-one
cheer dance.

132
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,867
Wannabes versus the sqquad.

133
00:08:24,233 --> 00:08:25,267
Who wants to go first?

134
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:27,933
Me.

135
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:30,667
All right, Mookie.

136
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,733
Since you are an attention
seeker, you go first.

137
00:08:33,867 --> 00:08:37,067
You versus me,
the squad captain.

138
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,333
Deal!

139
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:40,300
Bring it on!

140
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:42,333
Places!

141
00:08:43,767 --> 00:08:44,733
Music!

142
00:08:56,633 --> 00:08:58,267
Let's go, Mookie!

143
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,067
You're out!

144
00:09:32,333 --> 00:09:33,600
What do you mean I'm out?

145
00:09:33,733 --> 00:09:35,233
You tripped me!

146
00:09:35,367 --> 00:09:38,433
Oh, do you have proof?

147
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:40,233
Maybe you're just such
a weakling!

148
00:09:40,367 --> 00:09:41,733
Maybe you're describing
yourself?

149
00:09:41,867 --> 00:09:48,433
- Mookie! Stop that!
- Stop! Stacey!

150
00:09:48,567 --> 00:09:49,433
Stop that!

151
00:09:49,567 --> 00:09:51,367
- Stacey, let her go!
- Mookie!

152
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,333
Stop that!

153
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:55,800
- Now what?
- That's enough!

154
00:09:55,933 --> 00:09:58,167
Calm down!
Can you please stop them?

155
00:09:58,300 --> 00:10:02,500
- Mookie! Enough! No!
- That's enough! Now what?

156
00:10:02,667 --> 00:10:05,033
Let her go.

157
00:10:05,167 --> 00:10:06,733
- Approach them.
- Mookie!

158
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:09,233
- Mookie!
- Mookie! That's enough

159
00:10:09,367 --> 00:10:11,500
Stop that!

160
00:10:11,633 --> 00:10:13,200
No!

161
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:14,367
What?

162
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:16,600
That's enough!
Come on!

163
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,267
Now what?

164
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:21,333
Enough!

165
00:10:21,467 --> 00:10:24,100
You will never come near
my niece again!

166
00:10:24,233 --> 00:10:25,900
I am not yet done with you!

167
00:10:26,033 --> 00:10:27,233
You better watch out!

168
00:10:27,367 --> 00:10:29,233
I will report you
to the principal,

169
00:10:29,367 --> 00:10:31,033
and I will make sure
you will pay for this!

170
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,067
Go!

171
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:36,933
Let's go!

172
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:38,333
Are you ok?

173
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:44,367
If you did not stop me,
she would have been bald by now!

174
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:46,467
You did the right thing, Mookie.

175
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,167
It's just right
that you fought her.

176
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,367
She deserves it.

177
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:52,933
Are you sure you're okay?

178
00:10:53,067 --> 00:10:54,033
Yes.

179
00:10:55,633 --> 00:10:56,667
Let's go.

180
00:10:57,967 --> 00:10:59,233
My bag.

181
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:16,933
So annoying!

182
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:18,033
Mookie!

183
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:26,333
I hate you, Stacey!

184
00:11:26,467 --> 00:11:29,633
- Mookie, dear.
- You are so annoying!

185
00:11:29,767 --> 00:11:31,033
Baby girl!

186
00:11:31,167 --> 00:11:32,600
I hate you so much!

187
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:35,600
Calm down.
It's okay.

188
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,233
That's enough.

189
00:11:39,567 --> 00:11:44,800
She's so annoying!
I hate her so much!

190
00:11:44,967 --> 00:11:46,567
Mookie!

191
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:47,667
Mookie!

192
00:11:49,767 --> 00:11:50,867
Danilo...

193
00:11:52,067 --> 00:11:54,567
I will just talk to Mookie.
Let's go.

194
00:11:58,100 --> 00:11:59,533
Your principal just called me.

195
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,033
They said you got into a fight?

196
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:05,800
You physically hurt
your classmate.

197
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:07,567
She started it.

198
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:09,133
She tripped me.

199
00:12:09,267 --> 00:12:10,900
It was her fault.

200
00:12:11,933 --> 00:12:14,433
Maybe she thought I would just
let it slip.

201
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,633
Of course not!

202
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:17,033
That's enough, Danilo.

203
00:12:17,167 --> 00:12:19,633
I saw how that lady undermined
Mookie.

204
00:12:19,767 --> 00:12:21,233
Your daughter did
the right thing!

205
00:12:21,367 --> 00:12:22,967
No.

206
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,533
That's not right!

207
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,100
Mookie, come here.

208
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,433
What is happening to you?

209
00:12:31,067 --> 00:12:33,700
Your mom and I did not raise you
that way.

210
00:12:35,433 --> 00:12:39,000
That's because I learned
how to fight, Dad!

211
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:41,667
Should I always be
the bigger person?

212
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:46,000
Mookie, you do not have
to get even at all times!

213
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:47,100
You don't have to fight all
the time!

214
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:49,200
And not at all times,
they can bully me, Dad!

215
00:12:49,367 --> 00:12:51,300
Do not talk back to me
like that!

216
00:12:51,433 --> 00:12:53,067
And do not raise your voice
at me.

217
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:56,233
Mookie, I am still you father.

218
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,433
Did you think I wouldn't notice
what you're doing?

219
00:13:00,567 --> 00:13:04,267
You always go out,
and drink alcohol.

220
00:13:06,367 --> 00:13:09,333
I just let you.

221
00:13:09,467 --> 00:13:11,633
But that's going to stop.

222
00:13:11,767 --> 00:13:13,433
Because as soon
as your classes ends,

223
00:13:13,567 --> 00:13:15,600
I want you to go home straight.

224
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:19,100
You will not go out
with your friends!

225
00:13:19,233 --> 00:13:21,033
Do you understand?

226
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,467
Am I grounded?

227
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:24,333
Yes! You are grounded!

228
00:13:24,467 --> 00:13:26,300
So go to your room now!

229
00:13:30,667 --> 00:13:32,800
Go inside!

230
00:13:35,767 --> 00:13:40,467
Danilo, just relax...

231
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,533
I don't understand, Auntie!

232
00:13:51,667 --> 00:13:57,433
Why do I always feel like dad
does not understand me anymore?

233
00:14:01,267 --> 00:14:03,200
I feel like I have no one
on my side.

234
00:14:05,067 --> 00:14:08,167
I think you are the only person
who understands me.

235
00:14:10,233 --> 00:14:12,767
Of course, baby girl.

236
00:14:13,567 --> 00:14:16,367
I am by your side forever
and ever.

237
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:18,433
I have an idea.

238
00:14:19,467 --> 00:14:23,067
Let's just pretend
that you obeyed your father.

239
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,200
I got you.

240
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:28,200
You can still do whatever
you want to do.

241
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:30,433
And I'll be the one
to cover for you.

242
00:14:30,567 --> 00:14:31,567
Is that okay?

243
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:33,333
Really, Auntie?

244
00:14:33,467 --> 00:14:34,800
Yeah.

245
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:38,367
Just make sure you will
tell me everything you do

246
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:40,400
and the places you go to.

247
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:42,767
What?

248
00:14:45,133 --> 00:14:50,567
So that I can tell you
what I told your dad.

249
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:52,167
We have to be in sync
with our alibis.

250
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:56,033
- Yehey, thank you!
- You're welcome!

251
00:15:04,933 --> 00:15:06,833
This is not right, Logan.

252
00:15:06,967 --> 00:15:08,867
Jade is already poisoning
my daughter's mind

253
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,133
and whole persona.

254
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:13,867
That woman is a pest.

255
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:17,733
She didn't change.
She chaged a lot.

256
00:15:17,867 --> 00:15:20,433
I want to talk to my mom
about this.

257
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:23,300
But I cannot reach her.

258
00:15:23,433 --> 00:15:26,200
I also want to call Wiro
and Kutsy to ask for updates.

259
00:15:27,433 --> 00:15:29,333
What if I just ask mom
for a meet-up?

260
00:15:29,467 --> 00:15:30,433
Don't.

261
00:15:32,033 --> 00:15:33,800
Don't to that.

262
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:37,667
If Jade finds out,
you might be in danger.

263
00:15:38,933 --> 00:15:39,833
Just don't.

264
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:41,433
Wait until you meet with Jade.

265
00:15:42,633 --> 00:15:46,000
I think this is the right time
for me to confrotn Jade.

266
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,867
What's your plan?

267
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,200
Go to her house?

268
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:54,500
I received an inuiry
from Artemis.

269
00:15:54,633 --> 00:15:58,267
That's Olive's company
and now Jade is running it.

270
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:10,533
They want to book
the bar for an event.

271
00:16:10,700 --> 00:16:12,400
I want to accept the offer

272
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:15,967
because I think
this is the right time for me

273
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:17,767
and Jade to finally meet.

274
00:16:17,900 --> 00:16:20,900
This is the right time
to get Mookie back.

275
00:16:27,233 --> 00:16:29,367
You still haven't found Emma?

276
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:32,800
I'm sorry.
I still don't have any lead.

277
00:16:32,933 --> 00:16:36,033
And I've been busy
with the event.

278
00:16:36,167 --> 00:16:37,700
The bar has finally confirmed.

279
00:16:37,833 --> 00:16:40,167
Now we're sure that we have
an event venue.

280
00:16:41,033 --> 00:16:42,033
That's good to know.

281
00:16:42,300 --> 00:16:45,000
I thought you would also fail
in that aspect.

282
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:55,867
Mookie, my child,

283
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:59,667
let's eat.
Your breakfast is ready.

284
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:01,400
Mookie...

285
00:17:01,967 --> 00:17:02,467
Love...

286
00:17:03,367 --> 00:17:05,167
- Jade...
- Just let her be.

287
00:17:08,233 --> 00:17:10,333
I am just worried with Mookie.

288
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:19,267
I feel like it's my fault
why she is acting this way.

289
00:17:19,433 --> 00:17:21,467
No. Don't think that way.

290
00:17:23,267 --> 00:17:27,133
I feel like it's my fault.

291
00:17:27,267 --> 00:17:30,967
I encouraged her to fight.

292
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:34,067
I didn't think she would
overdo it.

293
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:36,800
Maybe it's because of her
trauma with my sister.

294
00:17:42,267 --> 00:17:44,567
Just let her be for now.
Don't worry too much.

295
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:49,800
Of course, I want the two of you
to get along.

296
00:17:50,867 --> 00:17:53,333
And the time will come
that that will happen.

297
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:57,700
Let's have breakfast now.

298
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,000
I will not be easy on you, okay?

299
00:18:31,367 --> 00:18:32,667
Logan...

300
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:38,467
Okay, okay, okay! It's fine.
Okay now.

301
00:18:49,367 --> 00:18:50,567
I'm done in the gym.

302
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:51,867
I will go see Mookie now.

303
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,300
I just want to see her.

304
00:18:53,433 --> 00:18:55,167
What if Jade is there?

305
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:56,800
You will get caught.

306
00:18:56,933 --> 00:18:57,833
I will be careful!

307
00:18:57,967 --> 00:18:59,500
Emma...

308
00:18:59,633 --> 00:19:01,433
No matter how careful you are,

309
00:19:01,567 --> 00:19:02,767
if you do not have anything
to protect yourself,

310
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:05,933
you are just like a beggar on
the streets who sells eggs.

311
00:19:06,067 --> 00:19:09,333
If someone wanted to get you,
they will.

312
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:11,667
Put your bag down.

313
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:18,000
We will teach you basic
self defense.

314
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:23,167
No matter how angelic
your face is,

315
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:26,967
you have to know how to fight
back when they hurt you.

316
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:28,800
Marco, come here.

317
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:33,633
Real danger is not always
visible.

318
00:19:33,767 --> 00:19:35,733
Sometimes, it's just right
behind you.

319
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:40,000
You have to be alert
all the time.

320
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:44,467
So you can fight the enemy...

321
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:48,967
And control him, so you can find
their weakness.

322
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:51,133
That's where you will strike.

323
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:56,833
Let's try it?

324
00:19:58,433 --> 00:19:59,400
Thank you, Marco.

325
00:20:05,167 --> 00:20:06,267
Ready?

326
00:20:10,033 --> 00:20:11,533
Sorry!

327
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:13,400
Hello, Astrid?

328
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:15,933
Why are you not yet
in the office?

329
00:20:16,067 --> 00:20:16,933
Where are you?

330
00:20:18,367 --> 00:20:19,333
What hospital?

331
00:20:20,967 --> 00:20:22,633
You fell?

332
00:20:22,767 --> 00:20:24,033
Wow, Astrid!

333
00:20:24,167 --> 00:20:26,833
Right in the middle
of our workload?

334
00:20:26,967 --> 00:20:28,933
Fine! Update me!

335
00:20:29,067 --> 00:20:33,667
Ma'am Jade, you have a visitor.
She wanted to get inside.

336
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,433
- Who? Let her in.
- She's there.

337
00:21:06,733 --> 00:21:07,733
Leticia?

338
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:10,800
What are you doing here?

339
00:21:12,133 --> 00:21:13,167
Jade?

340
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,867
I'm guilty.

341
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,233
I was a bad best friend
to your sister.

342
00:21:22,733 --> 00:21:26,267
She's now gone,
and I did not visit her.

343
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:29,667
That's fine.

344
00:21:31,267 --> 00:21:35,133
I'm sure Olive has already
forgiven you.

345
00:21:36,633 --> 00:21:37,300
No.

346
00:21:38,533 --> 00:21:40,733
I know your sister so well.

347
00:21:40,867 --> 00:21:42,367
She does not know
how to forgive.

348
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:45,100
Of course not.

349
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:48,667
Olive is such a good person.

350
00:21:49,967 --> 00:21:54,000
No. We both have mental issues.

351
00:21:54,133 --> 00:21:55,567
That's why we're close!

352
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:56,767
We have the same personality!

353
00:21:58,267 --> 00:22:00,067
You are the only
bad person here, Leticia!

354
00:22:03,233 --> 00:22:05,400
Olive trusted you!

355
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:13,533
You were the only one she ever
had when everybody left her.

356
00:22:13,667 --> 00:22:14,933
But what did you do?

357
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:17,833
You turned your back away
from her.

358
00:22:21,233 --> 00:22:23,833
I am guilty of that, Jade.

359
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:27,367
That's why I'm here.
I want to ask for forgiveness.

360
00:22:29,033 --> 00:22:32,400
You don't deserve
to be forgiven!

361
00:22:32,533 --> 00:22:33,567
You left me!

362
00:22:34,933 --> 00:22:38,933
Just when I needed a friend,
you betrayed me!

363
00:22:39,067 --> 00:22:40,033
Left you?

364
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:44,133
What are you talking about,
Jade?

365
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:47,733
You even made a promise!

366
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:53,100
Best friends for all eternity!

367
00:22:54,533 --> 00:22:58,200
But you cannot fulfill
that promise!

368
00:23:04,333 --> 00:23:07,967
Back to back, soul to soul.

369
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:10,867
Never apart.

370
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:14,200
Always whole.

371
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:17,267
Wait a minute...

372
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,733
Do you still remember that?

373
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:23,200
Wait...

374
00:23:23,333 --> 00:23:24,733
How did you know that?

375
00:23:26,167 --> 00:23:28,100
That's our secret code.

376
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:34,933
My god, you're not Jade!

377
00:23:35,067 --> 00:23:36,100
Olive?

378
00:23:53,533 --> 00:23:56,433
Please. You have to help me
look after Mookie.

379
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:59,033
I heard Stacey and her squad.

380
00:23:59,167 --> 00:24:01,600
They are planning something
against her.

381
00:24:01,733 --> 00:24:02,600
What?

382
00:24:02,733 --> 00:24:05,667
We have to learn every step
Jade takes.

383
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:09,233
So we can strategize how
I can fight against her.

384
00:24:09,367 --> 00:24:11,033
Just observe her.

385
00:24:11,167 --> 00:24:12,633
You have to know her every move.

386
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:17,067
Her name is Emma Joseco.

387
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:19,933
If I find her, what shall I do?

388
00:24:20,067 --> 00:24:22,067
I want you to get rid of her.

389
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:23,833
I feel bad for Mookie.

390
00:24:23,967 --> 00:24:25,100
She doesn't have Emma.

391
00:24:25,233 --> 00:24:27,967
Her grandmother is missing
in action.

392
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:30,700
Don't you have any news
about Mom Ligaya?

393
00:24:35,033 --> 00:24:36,033
What's that?
